'''Azzedine Ounahi''' ({{Langx|ar|عز الدين أوناحي}}, {{IPA|ar|ʕiz ʔad.di:n u:na:ħi:|pron}}; born 19 April 2000) is a Moroccan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Girona FC|Girona]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|564548}}</ref>

Ounahi made his international debut in 2022, after previously being [[Cap (sport)|capped]] by the nation's youth teams at [[Morocco national under-20 football team|under-20]] level. He was chosen in Morocco's squad for the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]]. He was also picked for the [[Africa Cup of Nations]] in [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021]], [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023]] and [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations|2025]].

==Club career==

=== Early career ===
A former player of [[Raja CA]] and [[Mohammed VI Football Academy|Mohammed VI Academy]], Ounahi joined [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|RC Strasbourg]] in 2018. In August 2020, he moved to [[Championnat National]] club [[US Avranches|Avranches]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Azzeddine Ounahi (ex-Strasbourg) signe à Avranches|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-azzeddine-ounahi-ex-strasbourg-signe-a-avranches/1157767|date=3 August 2020|access-date=15 August 2021}}</ref>

=== Angers ===
On 14 July 2021, [[Ligue 1]] club [[Angers SCO|Angers]] announced the signing of Ounahi on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Angers recrute Azzedine Ounahi|url=https://www.footmercato.net/amp3453273236795645825-angers-recrute-azzedine-ounahi|date=14 July 2021|access-date=15 August 2021}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 15 August 2021 by scoring a goal in club's 3–0 league win against [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Angers vs. Lyon - 15 August 2021|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/08/15/france/ligue-1/angers-sporting-club-de-louest/olympique-lyonnais/3525912/|access-date=15 August 2021}}</ref>

=== Marseille ===
After attracting the interest of several top-tier clubs across Europe, thanks to his breakthrough performances for [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=23 December 2022 |title=Azzedine Ounahi : "Garder les pieds sur terres, continuer de travailler et surtout préparer la prochaine compétition" |url=https://www.angers-sco.fr/azzedine-ounahi-garder-les-pieds-sur-terres-continuer-de-travailler-et-surtout-preparer-la-prochaine-competition/ |access-date=29 January 2023 |website=Angers SCO |language=fr-FR}}</ref> on 29 January 2023 Ounahi officially joined fellow Ligue 1 side [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] for an estimated fee of 8 million [[euro]]s plus add-ons, signing a contract until June 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 January 2023 |title=Azzedine Ounahi est Olympien ! |url=https://www.om.fr/fr/actualites/4803/equipe-pro/72562-azzedine-ounahi-est-olympien |access-date=29 January 2023 |website=Olympique de Marseille |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Béal |first=Xavier |date=29 January 2023 |title=Montant du transfert, durée du contrat, salaire : toutes les infos sur la signature d'Ounahi à l'OM |url=https://www.goal.com/fr/news/montant-transfert-duree-contrat-salaire-toutes-infos-signature-ounahi-om/bltafa4abc43373d5e2 |access-date=29 January 2023 |website=Goal.com |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 1 February 2023, he scored his first goal for Marseille on his debut against [[FC Nantes|Nantes]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=PLAYER RATINGS {{!}} Nantes 0-2 Marseille: Azzedine Ounahi scores on debut as OM put pressure on PSG |url=https://onefootball.com/fr/news/player-ratings-nantes-0-2-marseille-azzedine-ounahi-scores-on-debut-as-om-put-pressure-on-psg-36715725 |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=OneFootball |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-02 |title=Azzedine Ounahi debuts for Marseille with flying colors |url=https://en.hespress.com/57968-azzedine-ounahi-debuts-for-marseille-with-flying-colors.html |access-date=2023-02-03 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> On 1 November 2023, Ounahi was nominated for the 2023 [[African Footballer of the Year]] by [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-11 |title=CAF announces CAF Awards 2023 Nominees for Men's Categories |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-announces-caf-awards-2023-nominees-for-men-s-categories/ |access-date=2023-11-01 |website=CAF |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==== Loan to Panathinaikos ====
On 4 September 2024, Ounahi joined Greek club [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] on an initial season-long loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web |title=Στον Παναθηναϊκό ο Αζεντίν Ουναΐ |url=https://www.pao.gr/transfers/ston-panathinaiko-o-azentin-ounai/ |publisher=Panathinaikos |access-date=4 September 2024 |language=Greek |date=4 September 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Azzedine Ounahi prêté au Panathinaïkos |url=https://www.om.fr/fr/actualites/4803/equipe-1ere/90861-azzedine-ounahi-prete-au-panathinaikos |publisher=Olympique de Marseille |access-date=4 September 2024 |language=French |date=4 September 2024 }}</ref>

=== Girona ===
On 30 August 2025, Ounahi signed with [[Girona FC|Girona]] on a contract lasting until 2030.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gironafc.cat/en/news/azzedine-ounahi-signed-until-2030 |title=Azzedine Ounahi, signed until 2030 |publisher=Girona FC |date=30 August 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Ounahi was called up for [[Morocco national under-20 football team|Morocco U20]] to participate in the [[Football at the 2018 Mediterranean Games|2018 Mediterranean Games]]. On 22 June 2018, he scored a goal at the 68th minute in a tie against [[Italy national under-18 football team|Italy]]. He later went on to win the bronze medal with the team after a victory in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]] against [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Pluie de médailles pour le Maroc aux Jeux méditerranéens de Tarragone|url=https://www.huffpostmaghreb.com/entry/pluies-de-medailles-pour-les-athletes-marocains-aux-jeux-mediterraneens-de-tarragone_mg_5b3773e9e4b08c3a8f6abaa4|date=30 August 2018|access-date=13 January 2022|language=es|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726143546/https://www.huffpostmaghreb.com/entry/pluies-de-medailles-pour-les-athletes-marocains-aux-jeux-mediterraneens-de-tarragone_mg_5b3773e9e4b08c3a8f6abaa4|archive-date=26 July 2018|url-status=usurped}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 23 December 2021, [[Vahid Halilhodžić]] gave Ounahi his first call-up to the [[Morocco national football team|Moroccan senior national team]] for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=23 December 2021|title=Vahid Halilhodzic reveals final list of players for CAN 2022|url=https://en.hespress.com/32767-vahid-halilhodzic-reveals-final-list-of-players-for-can-2022.html|access-date=13 January 2022|website=HESPRESS English - Morocco’s leading digital media|language=en-US}}</ref> Ounahi made his professional debut for Morocco in the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021 African Cup of Nations]] in a 1–0 victory against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] on 10 January 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Morocco vs. Ghana - Football Match Summary - January 10, 2022 - ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/618264|access-date=11 January 2022|website=ESPN.com|language=en}}</ref> In his fourth match with [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]], he managed to score a double in a 4–1 victory against [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF third round]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Salah, Partey, Uzoho: Africa's tops & flops from the World Cup playoffs {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-bh/lists/salah-partey-uzoho-africa-s-tops-and-flops-from-the-world/blt3309949022e87026#cs7ce2540058bfe7dc |access-date=1 April 2022 |website=www.goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=31 March 2022 |title=Azzedine Ounahi signe un doublé avec le Maroc |url=https://www.alsasports.fr/football/rc-strasbourg/les-anciens/azzedine-ounahi-signe-un-double-avec-le-maroc/42416/ |access-date=1 April 2022 |website=Alsa'Sports |language=fr-FR}}</ref> which marked his first goal with the national team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 March 2022 |title=المنتخب المغربي يُمطر شباك الكونغو برباعية.. ويتأهل إلى "مونديال 2022" |url=https://www.hespress.com/المنتخب-المغربي-يُمطر-شباك-الكونغو-بر-965905.html |access-date=1 April 2022 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=World Cup playoffs round-up: Portugal and Poland book their spots in Qatar finals |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/soccer/international/world-cup-playoffs-round-up-portugal-and-poland-book-their-spots-in-qatar-finals-1.4839634 |access-date=1 April 2022 |newspaper=The Irish Times |language=en}}</ref>

On 10 November 2022, he was named in Morocco's 26-man [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Morocco|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Qatar]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco World Cup 2022 squad: Who's in and who's out? {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-bh/lists/morocco-2022-world-cup-squad-hakimi-ziyech-mazraoui-qatar/blta36257fc4feeb66a |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=www.goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=10 November 2022 |title=Moroccan coach unveils list of 26 Atlas Lions in 2022 World Cup |url=https://en.hespress.com/52697-moroccan-coach-unveils-list-of-26-atlas-lions-in-2022-world-cup.html |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> After an impressive performance in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|round of 16]] game against [[Spain national football team|Spain]], which Morocco won on penalties, Spanish manager [[Luis Enrique]] commented on Ounahi's performance: "My God, where does this guy come from? I was pleasantly surprised by their number eight. I don't remember his name, I'm sorry…".<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |title= World Cup 2022: Bellingham, Gakpo, Fernandez and other breakout stars |work= BBC Sport |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63941734 |access-date=16 December 2022 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Azzedine Ounahi: Morocco's elegant, industrious midfielder counts Luis Enrique among his new admirers following breakout World Cup |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12040/12763918/azzedine-ounahi-moroccos-elegant-industrious-midfielder-counts-luis-enrique-among-his-new-admirers-following-breakout-world-cup |access-date=2023-01-01 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref> In the quarter-final match against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], which Morocco won 1–0, no Moroccan player had more [[Dribbling (association football)|dribbles]] (three) or won more duels (seven) than Ounahi.<ref>{{Cite news |title= World Cup 2022: Bellingham, Gakpo, Fernandez and other breakout stars |work= BBC Sport |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63941734 |access-date=16 December 2022 }}</ref> Morocco went on to finish fourth in the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-21 |title=Morocco WC team returns to heroes' reception |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/fifa-club-world-cup/story/4835857/morocco-receives-a-triumphant-homecoming-historic-fourth-place-at-the-2022-world-cup-in-qatar |access-date=2023-01-31 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> During a friendly match against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], which resulted in a 2–1 victory,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-26 |title=Morocco beats Brazil 2-1 in friendly |url=https://en.hespress.com/60951-morocco-beats-brazil-2-1-in-friendly.html |access-date=2023-04-01 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> Ounahi picked up an injury after suffering a fracture in his right toe,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-29 |title=Ounahi confirms injury during Morocco-Brazil friendly |url=https://en.hespress.com/61148-ounahi-confirms-injury-during-morocco-brazil-friendly.html |access-date=2023-04-01 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> that required to undergo surgery, which resulted in an end of his football season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-30 |title=Azzedine Ounahi out for rest of the season due to injury |url=https://en.hespress.com/61234-azzedine-ounahi-out-for-rest-of-the-season-due-to-injury.html |access-date=2023-04-01 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-31 |title=Ounahi 'very disappointed' following season-ending injury |url=https://en.hespress.com/61281-ounahi-very-disappointed-following-season-ending-injury.html |access-date=2023-04-01 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 17 January 2024, Ounahi scored a goal in a 3–0 victory against [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]], marking his first ever goal in the [[Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-17 |title=Morocco break North Africa's AFCON curse beating Tanzania 3-0 |url=https://en.hespress.com/78281-morocco-break-north-africas-afcon-curse-beating-tanzania-3-0.html |access-date=2024-01-17 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, Ounahi was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Ounahi considers [[Andrés Iniesta]] his footballing role model. Ounahi is the cousin of footballer Reda Mhannaoui.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Angers Sco. Azzedine Ounahi : « Au quartier, pour m'en sortir, je devais jouer technique »|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/angers-sco/angers-sco-azzedine-ounahi-au-quartier-pour-m-en-sortir-je-devais-jouer-technique-81b1c630-4d4f-11ec-a0f2-c7fe53b09c00|language=fr|date=25 November 2021|access-date=5 September 2025}}</ref>

